race.comment: FRIDGE MONSTER (4) is flying of late, winning four of his past six, dominant on heavy ground at Geelong last start when powering away to score by nearly four lengths. No issue whatsoever to 1600m and the firmer footing this time around is no query either. Can continue his strong run of recent form. FLYING VALLEY (3) has been below his best the past couple but his best is good enough. He maps for a soft run in transit and dropping back to the mile now may be what's best for him. Can turn his form around. KENGERO (5) was backed in the Country Final at Flemington last time, he'll be fitter again. MARGIE'S BOY (7) is not out of this on recent form.
